r of FIRE,\u00a0 JL Collins.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"middle\" width=\" 200\"><a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/3N4Dhzm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-64842\" style=\"margin-top: 60px;\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/the-psychology-of-money-book.jpg\" alt=\"the psychology of money\" width=\"500\" height=\"773\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/the-psychology-of-money-book.jpg 500w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/the-psychology-of-money-book-194x300.jpg 194w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/the-psychology-of-money-book-323x500.jpg 323w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/a><\/td>\n<td style=\"padding-top: 20px;\" valign=\"center\"><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/3N4Dhzm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">The Psychology of Money<\/a><\/strong> by <strong>Morgan Housel<\/strong> &#8212; A fun newer book that dissects just what makes the financial decisions in our lives, and surprisingly it&#8217;s much more emotional than rational! In his clever, well-written, way, Morgan shares 19 short stories exploring the strange ways people think about money and how to use this to make better decisions of our own. One of my favorite writers I follow on Twitter as well: <a href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/morganhousel\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@MorganHousel<\/a><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"middle\" width=\" 200\"><a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/3LXoSU5\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-64829\" style=\"margin-top: 45px;\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/the-power-of-less-book.jpg\" alt=\"the power of less\" width=\"302\" height=\"455\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/the-power-of-less-book.jpg 302w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/the-power-of-less-book-199x300.jpg 199w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 302px) 100vw, 302px\" \/><\/a><\/td>\n<td style=\"padding-top: 20px;\" valign=\"center\"><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/3LXoSU5\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">The Power of Less<\/a><\/strong> by <strong>Leo Babauta<\/strong> &#8212; One of my favorite minimalism books! I ready this over 10 years ago and it completely shifted my mindset to be more conscious about what I bring into my home, what I keep, and ultimately what I release back into the world for the best balance of &#8220;stuff&#8221;\/freedom. Lots of practical advice here, as well as the more *mental* aspects of minimalism too since it all resides in our HEADS just as much as the physical world. Gotta clear up all areas of our lives to make room for the stuff we love the most! Leo also runs a fantastic OG blog on the same matter at <a href=\"https:\/\/zenhabits.net\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ZenHabits.net<\/a><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"middle\" width=\" 200\"><a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/3wTRB7P\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-64831\" style=\"margin-top: 65px;\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/essentialism.jpg\" alt=\"essentialism\" width=\"332\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/essentialism.jpg 332w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/essentialism-199x300.jpg 199w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 332px) 100vw, 332px\" \/><\/a><\/td>\n<td valign=\"center\"><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/3wTRB7P\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Essentialism<\/a><\/strong> by <strong>Greg McKeown<\/strong>&#8212; One of my favorite books in the entire world, this was the one that drastically changed my work\/life balance and got me towards my dream lifestyle!! While businessy in nature, it focuses more on taking control of your LIFE and what you care about (and don&#8217;t), and helping you find a much more efficient way to manage everything important to you, like jobs\/passions\/family\/projects\/dreams\/etc. <strong><em>Keep what is absolutely essential, then eliminate the rest!<\/em><\/strong> Highly enjoyable read. You can see my write up on it <a href=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/essentialism-book-review-life-changer\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">here<\/a>.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td valign=\"middle\" width=\" 200\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-68339 size-full\" style=\"margin-top: 40px;\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/red-book-coins-2025.jpg\" alt=\"red book - coins - 2025\" width=\"390\" height=\"522\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/red-book-coins-2025.jpg 390w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/red-book-coins-2025-224x300.jpg 224w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/red-book-coins-2025-374x500.jpg 374w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 390px) 100vw, 390px\" \/><\/td>\n<td style=\"padding-top: 20px;\" valign=\"center\"><strong><a href=\"https:\/\/amzn.to\/4f2FAjj\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">A Guide Book of US Coins 2025<\/a><\/strong> by <strong>R.S. Yeoman<\/strong>&#8212; AKA &#8220;The Red Book&#8221; for coin collectors that&#8217;s basically our bible for looking up coins and how much they&#8217;re worth ;) I know this book doesn&#8217;t fit in here, but maybe it gets ONE of you to take up this beautiful hobby of the kings and join me in the fun!! Or at least consider this as a gift to a young person in your life that expresses an interest in our nation&#8217;s coinage &#x1f44d;<\/p>\n<p>(For more coin loving, check out my blog &#8211; <a href=\"https:\/\/cointhrill.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">CoinThrill.com<\/a> &#8211; or hit me up if you ever need help <a href=\"https:\/\/jmoney.biz\/coin-help\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">valuing or inventorying or liquidating<\/a> a coin collection.)<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<h2>Favorite Financial Apps &amp; Services:<\/h2>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<table